title: Aretha Franklin (1942 - 2018), the Queen of Soul
description:
Aretha Franklin, affectionately called the "Queen of Soul," died Thursday, August 16, 2018. Blessed with an incredible voice, she was a giant of soul music. Franklin’s signature song was her version of Otis Redding’s “Respect,” released in 1967. Her many hit songs included “(You Make Me Feel Like) A Natural Woman,” “Freeway of Love,” and “Rock Steady.” We remember her life and legacy this memorial tribute video.
